<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-56-0154 </DOCNO><TEXT>In 1986, 60% of the loaders in German quarries were hydraulic excavators.The success of large (60-500 tonne) hydraulic excavators lies in theirlong lifetimes, high loading performance, high availability, low energyconsumption, minimal need for auxiliary machines and positive effectson costs in both advancing and tailing mining systems. These factorsare discussed. The outlook for the equipment manufacturers is bright.2 figs.</TEXT></DOC>